Add dedup logic inside `recordTimelineFrame()` in `/Users/shivam94/.pi/agent/extensions/orchestrator/plan-panel.ts` to skip frames where state hasn't meaningfully changed.

Read the file, find the `recordTimelineFrame` function. Replace it with this:

```typescript
export function recordTimelineFrame(
    event: string,
    feedState?: Record<string, unknown> | null,
    feedRender?: string,
): void {
    const entry = {
        t: Date.now() - _timelineStart,
        event,
        render: snapshotPlanRender(),
        state: inspectPlanState(),
        ...(feedState !== undefined ? { feedState } : {}),
        ...(feedRender !== undefined ? { feedRender } : {}),
    };

    // Dedup: skip if last frame has same event + identical state + identical feedState
    const last = _timeline[_timeline.length - 1];
    if (last && last.event === entry.event) {
        const stateSame = JSON.stringify(last.state) === JSON.stringify(entry.state);
        const feedSame = JSON.stringify(last.feedState ?? null) === JSON.stringify(entry.feedState ?? null);
        if (stateSame && feedSame) {
            return; // Nothing meaningful changed — skip
        }
    }

    if (_timeline.length >= MAX_TIMELINE_FRAMES) _timeline.shift();
    _timeline.push(entry);
}
```

This collapses consecutive same-event frames with identical state/feedState into a single frame. The first frame of each event type is kept (tracks the transition moment), subsequent identical frames are dropped.

Do NOT change anything else in the file. Verify with a read after edit.

